Digital entity.EditorialNote: This is a proxy class to be replaced by its OBI equivalent, once there is an official release built off BFO v1.1 that can be successfully classified using Pellet v1.5.0 in Protege.
Digital entity.Comment: OBI has this as a child of "non realizable information entity";  we may need to update the entire hierarchy (MEM)
Digital entity.Definition: A digital entity is an information entity which is a collection of bits that can be interpreted by a computer. Two digital entities are the same if they are bitwise identical.
